Citations
Date: 5/6/1860
Source: Colonist (Nelson)
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: No. 1 Volunteer Company took some time to fill up its ranks, and No. 2 was completely in abeyance till an order arrived to embody the Militia;  when, from a horror of blue frocks, highlows, and other "vulgaw" matters, a rush was made to swear loyalty to our government, and thus No. 2 was quickly filled to the bung;  no samples have yet been taken.
